The paper presents a solution to problems in reinforcement learning, specifically targeting the curse of dimensionality with continuous or large action sets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms and convergence, which could place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on policy-gradient algorithms and function approximation, which are common topics in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
